As per the title, this is a bug, where the PR gets unlinked from the build when a build is a rerun of a build which was triggered by a PR.

Steps to reproduce:

# Create a new PR on a branch that has pull requests builds enabled;
# Merge the PR and close the base branch;
# Re-run the build that was triggered by the PR;
# The link to the PR of the build will not show up, and env variables that use the PR will not work too.

This is a problem because, as you can see on the attached image, the PR cannot be referenced within the build.

